title: For Sale:  Common Sense
postcontent: Since some of us out there need some clarification.1. READ THE AD.Read the entire ad before contacting someone. This should be self explanatory.2. LOWBALLING.Negotiating a fair price with someone is one thing, offering them half their asking price is just disrespectful. Do your research and be reasonable with your offers.3. BOTTOM DOLLAR.Refer to #2. Asking this basically means "stand by for lowballing." Don't waste people's time with this.4. NO TRADES.When someone puts this in their ad, it generally means they are not interested in trades of ANY kind. Assume that your item is no exception. While ultimately harmless, unsolicited trade offers are still rude and irritating.5. "I SEEN IT CHEAPER."We're not stupid. If you had in fact found it cheaper, you would have bought it there. Armslist is not a Wal-Mart, there is no price-match guarantee. 6. PACKAGE DEALS.If someone is selling a gun, optic or other item with accessories specific to their item, do not expect them to sell the main item separately for a reduced price. If you don't have a use for it, they probably don't either, especially if they sell the item it goes to.7. FOLLOW THROUGH.More of a common courtesy thing, but worth mentioning. If you tell someone you're interested and then change your mind, please let them know. It only takes a few seconds to send an email or text and tell them you went a different route. Telling someone you want to buy their stuff and then just blowing them off is not cool.Thanks for reading, stay safe and have a nice day.
